Hancock Mezzanine Investments – Company Profile


Mezzanine financing company overviewMezzanine firm logo:Headquarters location:United StatesTypical mezzanine financing range:UndisclosedGeographic focus:United StatesIndustry focus:Industry agnostic
Company profile
Listed in the following regions:North America USA Alabama Arkansas Arizona California Colorado Connecticut Delaware Florida Georgia Iowa Idaho Illinois Indiana Kansas Kentucky Louisiana Massachusetts Maryland Maine Michigan Minnesota Missouri Mississippi Montana North Carolina North Dakota Nebraska New Hampshire New Jersey New Mexico Nevada New York Ohio Oklahoma Oregon Pennsylvania Rhode Island South Carolina South Dakota Tennessee Texas Utah Virginia Vermont Washington Wisconsin West Virginia Wyoming 
Hancock Capital Management, LLC provides junior capital to support the business objectives of experienced management teams and shareholders. Their sources of capital are John Hancock Life Insurance Company USA (JHUSA) and its affiliates and certain client accounts, including their mezzanine funds. Their team of investment professionals has a deep base of investment experience across a wide variety of industries. This investment experience, in addition to their long-term investment focus, makes the firm a trusted partner.
Hancock Capital Management has been sourcing private debt investment opportunities for John Hancock and the firm’s third-party mezzanine funds since 1998. Since inception, the fund has invested over $1.4 billion across over 80 portfolio companies. Their latest fifth mezzanine fund held its final close in 2013 with $619 million in capital commitments. Their limited partners include insurance companies, endowments, corporate pension plans, family offices and high net worth individuals. Their funds include:

Hancock Mezzanine Partners L.P., along with its co-investment vehicles (collectively, “Fund I”), a $425 million mezzanine capital pool, formed in August 1998 and fully invested as of September 2000.
Hancock Mezzanine Partners II, L.P., (“Fund II”), a $200 million mezzanine capital pool, formed in December 2001 and fully invested as of October 2003.
Hancock Mezzanine Partners III, L.P., along with its co-investment vehicles (collectively, “Fund III”), a $396 million mezzanine capital pool, formed in October 2003 and fully invested as of December 2007.
Hancock Capital Partners IV, L.P., along with its co-investment vehicles (collectively, “Fund IV”), a $449 million mezzanine capital pool, formed in September 2007 and fully invested as of September 2012.
Hancock Capital Partners V, L.P., along with its co-investment vehicles (collectively, “Fund V”), a $619 million mezzanine capital pool, formed in August 2012 and is actively investing

Investment philosophy/criteria
Hancock Capital Management provides junior capital to finance leveraged buyouts, corporate growth, acquisitions and balance sheet recapitalizations. The firm’s partners consider them a valuable investment partner due to the speed at which they make decisions, their long-term, patient approach towards building value, and deep investment experience and industry knowledge.
The firm can invest up to $100 million per transaction, with a minimum investment size of $15 million, through flexible debt solutions including:

Mezzanine
Second Lien
Holdco Notes
Structured Equity

Hancock Capital Management looks for companies interested in their mezzanine financing and with the following characteristics:

Headquartered in North America
Minimum EBITDA of $10 million
Proven management teams
Meaningful competitive position in target markets
Favorable free cash flow generation with the capacity for additional cash flow growth
Cyclical or non-cyclical
Operating and financial flexibility to manage through economic cycles

While the firm doesn’t have any specific target industry, they have previously provided mezzanine capital to the following industries:

Aerospace and Defense
Automotive
Business Services
Chemicals
Consumer
Distribution
Food and Commodities
Government Services
Healthcare
Manufacturing
Oilfield Services
Plastics and Packaging
